00:00:57.286 --> 00:00:59.206 A:middle
And your app can easily access

00:00:59.206 --> 00:01:00.826 A:middle
this global audience by

00:01:00.826 --> 00:01:02.516 A:middle
following some simple steps and

00:01:02.516 --> 00:01:03.336 A:middle
best practices.

00:01:03.616 --> 00:01:05.356 A:middle
And, in today's session, we will

00:01:05.356 --> 00:01:07.666 A:middle
talk about how Xcode makes it so

00:01:07.666 --> 00:01:09.246 A:middle
easy for you to add new

00:01:09.246 --> 00:01:11.476 A:middle
languages to make your app look

00:01:11.726 --> 00:01:13.376 A:middle
and feel local, which will allow

00:01:13.376 --> 00:01:14.236 A:middle
you to go global.

00:01:15.196 --> 00:01:17.146 A:middle
So there are three main topics

00:01:17.146 --> 00:01:18.316 A:middle
we will be covering today.

00:01:18.956 --> 00:01:20.726 A:middle
First, we will start with how to

00:01:20.726 --> 00:01:23.806 A:middle
make your code world ready, then

00:01:23.806 --> 00:01:24.726 A:middle
we will walk you through the

00:01:24.726 --> 00:01:26.396 A:middle
localization process in Xcode

00:01:26.396 --> 00:01:28.356 A:middle
and introduce new features we

00:01:28.356 --> 00:01:29.556 A:middle
added in Xcode 9.

00:01:30.956 --> 00:01:32.006 A:middle
Finally, and through the

00:01:32.006 --> 00:01:33.806 A:middle
presentation, we will talk about

00:01:33.866 --> 00:01:35.436 A:middle
testing and give you some best

00:01:35.436 --> 00:01:37.116 A:middle
practices to make sure that your

00:01:37.116 --> 00:01:39.426 A:middle
app works and looks great in all

00:01:39.426 --> 00:01:40.656 A:middle
languages that you support.

00:01:40.926 --> 00:01:43.036 A:middle
So let's start with

00:01:43.036 --> 00:01:43.856 A:middle
internationalization.

00:01:48.046 --> 00:01:49.666 A:middle
So internationalization is the

00:01:49.736 --> 00:01:51.296 A:middle
process of designing your

00:01:51.296 --> 00:01:53.436 A:middle
software so it can be adapted to

00:01:53.436 --> 00:01:55.496 A:middle
different languages and regions

00:01:55.806 --> 00:01:57.346 A:middle
without making code changes

00:01:57.346 --> 00:01:59.336 A:middle
every single time you are adding

00:01:59.336 --> 00:02:00.926 A:middle
a new language to your app.

00:02:01.676 --> 00:02:02.936 A:middle
So the point here is it

00:02:02.936 --> 00:02:04.836 A:middle
shouldn't matter which language

00:02:04.936 --> 00:02:06.256 A:middle
your app is running in.

00:02:06.796 --> 00:02:08.296 A:middle
If the language has short text

00:02:09.166 --> 00:02:12.196 A:middle
or long text or tall text or

00:02:12.196 --> 00:02:14.336 A:middle
even text or layout that flows

00:02:14.336 --> 00:02:16.326 A:middle
from right to left, your app

00:02:16.386 --> 00:02:17.526 A:middle
should be able to adapt

00:02:17.526 --> 00:02:19.046 A:middle
dynamically to all these

00:02:19.106 --> 00:02:19.686 A:middle
scenarios.

00:02:20.196 --> 00:02:22.996 A:middle
And the first step in

00:02:22.996 --> 00:02:25.456 A:middle
internationalization is managing

00:02:25.456 --> 00:02:26.116 A:middle
your strings.

00:02:26.786 --> 00:02:30.006 A:middle
Your app will be localized by

00:02:30.006 --> 00:02:32.036 A:middle
translators who would be working

00:02:32.036 --> 00:02:34.376 A:middle
with your strings and in this

00:02:34.376 --> 00:02:35.696 A:middle
localized string is there to

00:02:35.696 --> 00:02:37.776 A:middle
make it easier for you to create

00:02:37.956 --> 00:02:39.706 A:middle
localizable content for your

00:02:39.706 --> 00:02:41.186 A:middle
translators as well as

00:02:41.226 --> 00:02:42.716 A:middle
displaying the right text at the

00:02:42.816 --> 00:02:43.316 A:middle
right time.

00:02:44.116 --> 00:02:45.796 A:middle
So if your strings are coming

00:02:45.796 --> 00:02:47.606 A:middle
from a storyboard or a zip file

00:02:48.036 --> 00:02:49.376 A:middle
they're localizable by default,

00:02:49.376 --> 00:02:50.536 A:middle
so we don't need to worry about

00:02:50.536 --> 00:02:50.766 A:middle
those.

00:02:51.226 --> 00:02:52.596 A:middle
But sometimes you might have

00:02:52.646 --> 00:02:54.426 A:middle
some strings that are defined in

00:02:54.426 --> 00:02:55.856 A:middle
your source code that will be

00:02:55.856 --> 00:02:57.226 A:middle
displayed to the user, like

00:02:57.226 --> 00:02:59.336 A:middle
error messages or notifications;

00:02:59.336 --> 00:03:00.606 A:middle
if you would like to notify your

00:03:00.606 --> 00:03:01.656 A:middle
users about something.

00:03:02.036 --> 00:03:03.296 A:middle
And you want to make sure that

00:03:03.296 --> 00:03:04.496 A:middle
this translator is also

00:03:04.496 --> 00:03:05.146 A:middle
localizable.

00:03:05.716 --> 00:03:07.106 A:middle
And to do that you just need to

00:03:07.106 --> 00:03:08.796 A:middle
wrap those strings with NS

00:03:08.876 --> 00:03:09.716 A:middle
Localized String.

00:03:10.786 --> 00:03:12.826 A:middle
In addition to that you can use

00:03:13.006 --> 00:03:14.886 A:middle
NS Localized String as a format

00:03:15.046 --> 00:03:17.196 A:middle
string with localized language

00:03:17.246 --> 00:03:19.116 A:middle
format to get a localized and a

00:03:19.196 --> 00:03:20.076 A:middle
formatted string.

00:03:21.146 --> 00:03:22.386 A:middle
So here let's go through a quick

00:03:22.386 --> 00:03:23.276 A:middle
example together.

00:03:24.276 --> 00:03:25.796 A:middle
So here they have a label.

00:03:26.176 --> 00:03:27.796 A:middle
When I set its text to a string

00:03:27.826 --> 00:03:28.806 A:middle
called population.

00:03:29.196 --> 00:03:30.976 A:middle
So again, my string is hardcoded

00:03:30.976 --> 00:03:32.436 A:middle
and is not localizable.

00:03:33.126 --> 00:03:34.966 A:middle
To make it localizable, you just

00:03:34.966 --> 00:03:36.516 A:middle
need to wrap it with NS

00:03:36.516 --> 00:03:37.306 A:middle
Localized String.

00:03:37.616 --> 00:03:38.836 A:middle
And as you can see here on the

00:03:38.836 --> 00:03:40.596 A:middle
screen, NS Localized String

00:03:40.646 --> 00:03:43.016 A:middle
takes two arguments, your string

00:03:43.016 --> 00:03:43.766 A:middle
and a comment.

00:03:44.376 --> 00:03:45.976 A:middle
Comments here are really, really

00:03:45.976 --> 00:03:47.156 A:middle
important to provide to your

00:03:47.156 --> 00:03:49.086 A:middle
translators so they have context

00:03:49.086 --> 00:03:50.296 A:middle
about the string they are

00:03:50.296 --> 00:03:51.006 A:middle
translating.

00:03:51.746 --> 00:03:54.106 A:middle
And I would say most of the time

00:03:54.106 --> 00:03:55.446 A:middle
you just need to use NS

00:03:55.516 --> 00:03:57.666 A:middle
Localized String, but in some

00:03:57.666 --> 00:03:59.086 A:middle
cases when you're working on a

00:03:59.086 --> 00:04:00.826 A:middle
framework or a shared component

00:04:01.106 --> 00:04:02.636 A:middle
you might want to use NS

00:04:02.636 --> 00:04:04.156 A:middle
Localized String from table

00:04:04.476 --> 00:04:06.146 A:middle
where you specify the table name

00:04:06.286 --> 00:04:07.406 A:middle
where your strings are coming

00:04:07.406 --> 00:04:07.796 A:middle
from.

00:04:08.326 --> 00:04:11.526 A:middle
And as I mentioned before, you

00:04:11.526 --> 00:04:13.426 A:middle
can also combine NS Localized

00:04:13.426 --> 00:04:14.456 A:middle
String with Localized String

00:04:14.456 --> 00:04:17.176 A:middle
with Format, where NS Localized

00:04:17.176 --> 00:04:18.306 A:middle
String is a format string.

00:04:18.456 --> 00:04:19.906 A:middle
And in this case it's really,

00:04:19.906 --> 00:04:21.276 A:middle
really critical that you provide

00:04:21.276 --> 00:04:22.306 A:middle
those comments for your

00:04:22.306 --> 00:04:24.346 A:middle
translators so they have context

00:04:24.346 --> 00:04:25.626 A:middle
about the string they are

00:04:25.656 --> 00:04:26.266 A:middle
translating.

00:04:27.336 --> 00:04:30.946 A:middle
Then at run time NS Localized

00:04:30.946 --> 00:04:32.116 A:middle
String will determine the

00:04:32.176 --> 00:04:34.196 A:middle
preferred language of the user

00:04:34.686 --> 00:04:36.596 A:middle
and find the corresponding

00:04:36.596 --> 00:04:38.046 A:middle
localizable string files.

00:04:38.506 --> 00:04:39.876 A:middle
As you can see here, this is an

00:04:39.876 --> 00:04:41.986 A:middle
example of a localizable string

00:04:41.986 --> 00:04:43.796 A:middle
files coming from the French

00:04:43.796 --> 00:04:45.756 A:middle
localization projects and it

00:04:45.756 --> 00:04:47.306 A:middle
contains all your localizable

00:04:47.306 --> 00:04:48.266 A:middle
strings, the one that you

00:04:48.266 --> 00:04:49.976 A:middle
wrapped with NS Localized String

00:04:50.226 --> 00:04:51.486 A:middle
as well as the comments that you

00:04:51.486 --> 00:04:51.896 A:middle
provided.

00:04:51.896 --> 00:04:53.896 A:middle
And this is the information that

00:04:53.896 --> 00:04:54.586 A:middle
will be provided to your

00:04:54.586 --> 00:04:54.976 A:middle
translator.

00:04:59.116 --> 00:05:00.196 A:middle
And if you're using Objective

00:05:00.196 --> 00:05:01.936 A:middle
Senior App you can run the

00:05:01.936 --> 00:05:03.736 A:middle
static analyzer to find

00:05:03.736 --> 00:05:05.276 A:middle
localizability problems in your

00:05:05.276 --> 00:05:07.796 A:middle
code, like if you forgot to make

00:05:07.796 --> 00:05:09.516 A:middle
a string localizable or if you

00:05:09.516 --> 00:05:10.806 A:middle
forgot to add a comment to a

00:05:10.806 --> 00:05:13.356 A:middle
localizable string you can run

00:05:13.356 --> 00:05:14.776 A:middle
the static analyzer and you get

00:05:14.776 --> 00:05:16.526 A:middle
warnings that will show you what

00:05:16.526 --> 00:05:17.966 A:middle
these problems are and you can

00:05:17.966 --> 00:05:19.146 A:middle
fix them right on your code.

00:05:19.686 --> 00:05:20.786 A:middle
If you'd like to learn more

00:05:20.786 --> 00:05:22.366 A:middle
about the static analyzer please

00:05:22.396 --> 00:05:23.886 A:middle
check out this talk from last

00:05:23.886 --> 00:05:23.976 A:middle
year.

00:05:28.126 --> 00:05:29.506 A:middle
Another thing that your app

00:05:29.506 --> 00:05:31.036 A:middle
should handle well when it comes

00:05:31.096 --> 00:05:33.126 A:middle
to localization is working with

00:05:33.126 --> 00:05:35.056 A:middle
different visual representations

00:05:35.056 --> 00:05:37.566 A:middle
of date, time, numbers, et

00:05:37.566 --> 00:05:38.006 A:middle
cetera.

00:05:38.926 --> 00:05:41.596 A:middle
For example, 12-hour time format

00:05:41.746 --> 00:05:43.716 A:middle
is a standard format we use here

00:05:43.716 --> 00:05:45.466 A:middle
in the US, but you want to make

00:05:45.466 --> 00:05:47.556 A:middle
sure that a user who's using

00:05:47.556 --> 00:05:49.586 A:middle
your app in France, for example,

00:05:49.876 --> 00:05:51.316 A:middle
is getting 24-hour time

00:05:51.316 --> 00:05:52.686 A:middle
formatting set because this is

00:05:52.686 --> 00:05:53.916 A:middle
the default format used there.

00:05:55.166 --> 00:05:58.036 A:middle
And we provide a variety of very

00:05:58.086 --> 00:05:59.456 A:middle
powerful formatters that will

00:05:59.456 --> 00:06:01.166 A:middle
let you handle the complexity of

00:06:01.166 --> 00:06:03.566 A:middle
data formatting and regions, but

00:06:03.566 --> 00:06:04.826 A:middle
just to give you an example on

00:06:04.826 --> 00:06:06.466 A:middle
how formatters work, let's take

00:06:06.466 --> 00:06:07.726 A:middle
a look at a date formatter

00:06:07.726 --> 00:06:07.966 A:middle
example.

00:06:12.046 --> 00:06:13.346 A:middle
So here let's say you want to

00:06:13.346 --> 00:06:15.446 A:middle
display a full date format in

00:06:15.446 --> 00:06:16.426 A:middle
your app.

00:06:17.276 --> 00:06:20.136 A:middle
So instead of setting a date

00:06:20.136 --> 00:06:21.776 A:middle
format string that is specific

00:06:21.836 --> 00:06:23.766 A:middle
to a region or a country that

00:06:23.766 --> 00:06:25.746 A:middle
has a specific order, we

00:06:25.746 --> 00:06:27.566 A:middle
recommend that you use date

00:06:27.566 --> 00:06:27.986 A:middle
style.

00:06:29.136 --> 00:06:30.396 A:middle
This formatter has different

00:06:30.396 --> 00:06:31.956 A:middle
styles that you can choose from,

00:06:33.236 --> 00:06:34.296 A:middle
but since here we want to

00:06:34.296 --> 00:06:35.896 A:middle
display a full date format I'm

00:06:35.956 --> 00:06:37.306 A:middle
setting my date style to full.

00:06:37.686 --> 00:06:39.066 A:middle
So with that you are making sure

00:06:39.066 --> 00:06:40.486 A:middle
that your date is formatted

00:06:40.546 --> 00:06:42.686 A:middle
correctly in all regions in the

00:06:42.686 --> 00:06:42.986 A:middle
world.

00:06:43.496 --> 00:06:45.956 A:middle
As you can see on the screen,

00:06:45.956 --> 00:06:47.226 A:middle
there are differences between

00:06:47.226 --> 00:06:48.806 A:middle
the date format in the US and

00:06:48.806 --> 00:06:50.136 A:middle
the date format in France, like

00:06:50.136 --> 00:06:51.356 A:middle
the French date does not have

00:06:51.356 --> 00:06:53.076 A:middle
any commas, the month name is

00:06:53.076 --> 00:06:54.876 A:middle
not capitalized, the day of the

00:06:54.876 --> 00:06:56.056 A:middle
month comes before the month

00:06:56.056 --> 00:06:57.526 A:middle
itself, and this would not be

00:06:57.526 --> 00:07:00.006 A:middle
achievable if you have pasted in

00:07:00.316 --> 00:07:01.856 A:middle
a date format instead of a date

00:07:01.856 --> 00:07:01.976 A:middle
style.

00:07:05.106 --> 00:07:06.736 A:middle
In addition to date formatter,

00:07:06.916 --> 00:07:09.006 A:middle
we have a series of formatters

00:07:09.176 --> 00:07:10.976 A:middle
for common data types available

00:07:10.976 --> 00:07:11.776 A:middle
in foundation.

00:07:12.096 --> 00:07:13.226 A:middle
If you'd like to learn more

00:07:13.226 --> 00:07:14.576 A:middle
about formatters please check

00:07:14.576 --> 00:07:15.626 A:middle
out these two great talks from

00:07:15.626 --> 00:07:15.896 A:middle
last year.

00:07:20.166 --> 00:07:22.236 A:middle
Finally, you want to make sure

00:07:22.236 --> 00:07:23.656 A:middle
that your user interface is

00:07:23.726 --> 00:07:25.476 A:middle
flexible and looks nice and

00:07:25.476 --> 00:07:26.986 A:middle
beautiful in all languages that

00:07:26.986 --> 00:07:30.166 A:middle
you support and to do that the

00:07:30.166 --> 00:07:31.426 A:middle
process is really simple.

00:07:32.066 --> 00:07:33.166 A:middle
We just need to use base

00:07:33.166 --> 00:07:35.176 A:middle
internationalization and auto

00:07:35.176 --> 00:07:35.506 A:middle
layout.

00:07:36.186 --> 00:07:37.486 A:middle
So let's talk about base

00:07:37.486 --> 00:07:38.656 A:middle
internationalization for a

00:07:38.656 --> 00:07:39.086 A:middle
moment.

00:07:39.766 --> 00:07:42.196 A:middle
So by enabling base

00:07:42.196 --> 00:07:43.486 A:middle
internationalization in your

00:07:43.576 --> 00:07:46.066 A:middle
project, Xcode modifies your

00:07:46.136 --> 00:07:47.996 A:middle
projects for Destructor and

00:07:47.996 --> 00:07:50.286 A:middle
separates your UI from your

00:07:50.286 --> 00:07:53.126 A:middle
strings, which means any file

00:07:53.126 --> 00:07:54.526 A:middle
that is related to your user

00:07:54.526 --> 00:07:56.816 A:middle
interface, like a zip file or a

00:07:56.896 --> 00:07:59.016 A:middle
storyboard file, will be stored

00:07:59.116 --> 00:07:59.596 A:middle
in base [inaudible].

00:07:59.596 --> 00:08:03.376 A:middle
While your strings, either if

00:08:03.376 --> 00:08:04.176 A:middle
they are coming from a

00:08:04.176 --> 00:08:06.846 A:middle
storyboard file or if they are

00:08:06.886 --> 00:08:07.976 A:middle
in your code that you wrapped

00:08:07.976 --> 00:08:09.516 A:middle
with NS Localized String, they

00:08:09.516 --> 00:08:11.316 A:middle
will be stored in the specific

00:08:11.316 --> 00:08:14.426 A:middle
language folders so that way you

00:08:14.426 --> 00:08:15.976 A:middle
only have one set of user

00:08:15.976 --> 00:08:18.146 A:middle
interface instead of duplicating

00:08:18.146 --> 00:08:19.566 A:middle
your UI every single time you

00:08:19.566 --> 00:08:21.056 A:middle
are creating a new language in

00:08:21.846 --> 00:08:22.946 A:middle
your app.

00:08:23.176 --> 00:08:25.356 A:middle
And base internationalization is

00:08:25.356 --> 00:08:27.306 A:middle
enabled by default since Xcode

00:08:27.306 --> 00:08:27.666 A:middle
5.

00:08:27.746 --> 00:08:29.166 A:middle
So if you have an older project

00:08:29.166 --> 00:08:30.216 A:middle
that you want to localize,

00:08:30.546 --> 00:08:31.806 A:middle
please make sure that you enable

00:08:31.806 --> 00:08:31.976 A:middle
it there.

00:08:36.046 --> 00:08:36.956 A:middle
And you might be already

00:08:36.956 --> 00:08:38.866 A:middle
familiar with auto layout or

00:08:38.866 --> 00:08:39.966 A:middle
you're already using it to

00:08:39.966 --> 00:08:42.056 A:middle
support different presentations

00:08:42.056 --> 00:08:43.576 A:middle
of your app or different screen

00:08:43.576 --> 00:08:45.896 A:middle
sizes, but auto layout is also a

00:08:45.896 --> 00:08:48.296 A:middle
critical technology to use for

00:08:48.296 --> 00:08:49.076 A:middle
localization.

00:08:49.756 --> 00:08:51.356 A:middle
So by using auto layout you are

00:08:51.356 --> 00:08:52.806 A:middle
making sure that your app is

00:08:52.876 --> 00:08:54.576 A:middle
flexible and it can adapt to

00:08:54.576 --> 00:08:55.696 A:middle
different string lengths and

00:08:55.696 --> 00:08:57.186 A:middle
different configurations of your

00:08:57.736 --> 00:08:57.806 A:middle
app.

00:08:58.856 --> 00:09:00.866 A:middle
And new in Xcode 9 we are

00:09:00.866 --> 00:09:02.626 A:middle
introducing new interface

00:09:02.626 --> 00:09:04.476 A:middle
builder localization warnings to

00:09:04.476 --> 00:09:06.106 A:middle
validate your constraints for

00:09:06.106 --> 00:09:08.296 A:middle
localization, which means when

00:09:08.296 --> 00:09:10.186 A:middle
you are working on your UI and

00:09:10.186 --> 00:09:11.626 A:middle
your storyboard file or your zip

00:09:11.626 --> 00:09:12.816 A:middle
file and you're setting up these

00:09:12.866 --> 00:09:14.346 A:middle
constraints and they are not

00:09:14.346 --> 00:09:16.046 A:middle
localization friendly you will

00:09:16.046 --> 00:09:17.576 A:middle
get this warning as well as

00:09:17.616 --> 00:09:19.336 A:middle
suggestions on how to fix them.

00:09:20.396 --> 00:09:21.556 A:middle
And new interface builder

00:09:21.556 --> 00:09:23.336 A:middle
warnings will be available in

00:09:23.336 --> 00:09:24.176 A:middle
the future seat.

00:09:26.676 --> 00:09:28.726 A:middle
Additionally we are introducing

00:09:28.726 --> 00:09:30.166 A:middle
an Xcode -- 9 used to the

00:09:30.166 --> 00:09:32.376 A:middle
localization options for you to

00:09:32.376 --> 00:09:33.576 A:middle
simulate a localized

00:09:33.576 --> 00:09:34.156 A:middle
environment.

00:09:34.606 --> 00:09:36.466 A:middle
So instead of having a real

00:09:36.466 --> 00:09:38.336 A:middle
strings, translated strings, to

00:09:38.336 --> 00:09:39.836 A:middle
see how they look like in your

00:09:39.996 --> 00:09:41.196 A:middle
app you can just use one of

00:09:41.196 --> 00:09:42.766 A:middle
these pseudo localization

00:09:42.766 --> 00:09:44.196 A:middle
options that we are providing.

00:09:44.526 --> 00:09:45.896 A:middle
So, in Xcode 9, we have new

00:09:45.896 --> 00:09:47.346 A:middle
options for accented Latin

00:09:47.416 --> 00:09:49.366 A:middle
strings for a fixed strings and

00:09:49.366 --> 00:09:50.596 A:middle
new options for right to left

00:09:50.596 --> 00:09:51.076 A:middle
languages.

00:09:51.126 --> 00:09:53.786 A:middle
And with that I would like to

00:09:53.786 --> 00:09:56.236 A:middle
call Ia on stage to give you a

00:09:56.236 --> 00:09:57.776 A:middle
demo about how to prepare your

00:09:57.856 --> 00:09:58.846 A:middle
app for localization.

00:09:59.116 --> 00:09:59.496 A:middle
Thank you.

00:10:00.516 --> 00:10:06.500 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:10:07.096 --> 00:10:07.976 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Thank you, Sarah.

00:10:13.626 --> 00:10:15.576 A:middle
Hi. I'm Ia and today I want to

00:10:15.576 --> 00:10:17.136 A:middle
show you this really cool app

00:10:17.136 --> 00:10:18.266 A:middle
I've been working on called

00:10:18.266 --> 00:10:19.446 A:middle
International Effects.

00:10:20.026 --> 00:10:21.596 A:middle
As you see on the screen, my UI

00:10:21.596 --> 00:10:23.076 A:middle
consists mostly of this table

00:10:23.076 --> 00:10:25.146 A:middle
view and a user can go and

00:10:25.146 --> 00:10:26.946 A:middle
select a country or territory

00:10:26.946 --> 00:10:28.906 A:middle
from this list and they'll see

00:10:28.906 --> 00:10:30.126 A:middle
some information about it like

00:10:30.126 --> 00:10:32.776 A:middle
the flag, the population, and

00:10:32.776 --> 00:10:34.116 A:middle
even the language population.

00:10:35.566 --> 00:10:36.946 A:middle
So I made sure my app looks

00:10:37.046 --> 00:10:38.386 A:middle
beautiful in English and I'm

00:10:38.386 --> 00:10:40.366 A:middle
happy with the way it looks, but

00:10:40.646 --> 00:10:42.466 A:middle
now I want to internationalize

00:10:42.466 --> 00:10:43.876 A:middle
it so it can be ready for my

00:10:43.876 --> 00:10:44.966 A:middle
first localization.

00:10:45.676 --> 00:10:46.856 A:middle
And to do that I'm going to

00:10:46.856 --> 00:10:48.576 A:middle
follow the steps that Sarah just

00:10:48.576 --> 00:10:49.906 A:middle
showed us in her slides.

00:10:50.616 --> 00:10:51.936 A:middle
So the first thing I want to do

00:10:51.936 --> 00:10:53.306 A:middle
is my strings management.

00:10:54.096 --> 00:10:56.016 A:middle
I'm loading all of these strings

00:10:56.016 --> 00:10:57.646 A:middle
in my table cells in code.

00:10:57.646 --> 00:10:59.576 A:middle
So I'm going to open my Xcode

00:10:59.576 --> 00:10:59.976 A:middle
project.

00:11:06.546 --> 00:11:08.626 A:middle
And in my table view controller,

00:11:08.736 --> 00:11:10.646 A:middle
in my cell for wrote indexpath

00:11:10.646 --> 00:11:12.586 A:middle
function I want to make sure I

00:11:12.586 --> 00:11:14.366 A:middle
don't have any hardcoded strings

00:11:14.366 --> 00:11:16.406 A:middle
that I'm loading into my UI.

00:11:16.406 --> 00:11:18.266 A:middle
And instead I want to replace

00:11:18.266 --> 00:11:20.586 A:middle
them with a call to NS Localized

00:11:20.586 --> 00:11:20.866 A:middle
String.

00:11:21.606 --> 00:11:22.766 A:middle
And I'll pass in my English

00:11:22.766 --> 00:11:24.396 A:middle
string and I'll also give a

00:11:24.396 --> 00:11:25.206 A:middle
helpful comment.

00:11:25.366 --> 00:11:27.766 A:middle
So; "Label preceding the

00:11:27.766 --> 00:11:29.466 A:middle
selected territory."

00:11:29.796 --> 00:11:32.326 A:middle
And then I also went ahead and

00:11:32.326 --> 00:11:33.596 A:middle
made sure I'm calling NS

00:11:33.646 --> 00:11:35.336 A:middle
Localized String for all the

00:11:35.336 --> 00:11:36.656 A:middle
other text I'm loading in code.

00:11:37.746 --> 00:11:39.586 A:middle
So the next thing I want to do

00:11:39.586 --> 00:11:41.666 A:middle
is I also want to make sure I'm

00:11:41.666 --> 00:11:43.236 A:middle
displaying and representing data

00:11:43.236 --> 00:11:44.646 A:middle
correctly for different locales.

00:11:45.476 --> 00:11:48.406 A:middle
So in this case my data are

00:11:48.406 --> 00:11:50.086 A:middle
mostly these numbers that you're

00:11:50.086 --> 00:11:51.076 A:middle
seeing on the right side.

00:11:51.646 --> 00:11:52.956 A:middle
And numbers are displayed

00:11:52.956 --> 00:11:53.966 A:middle
differently in different

00:11:53.966 --> 00:11:54.416 A:middle
countries.

00:11:54.506 --> 00:11:57.176 A:middle
So to format them correctly I'm

00:11:57.326 --> 00:11:59.086 A:middle
going to use a number formatter.

00:12:00.526 --> 00:12:02.676 A:middle
Number formatter is similar to

00:12:03.596 --> 00:12:04.976 A:middle
date formatter that Sarah showed

00:12:04.976 --> 00:12:06.716 A:middle
us earlier, except, of course,

00:12:06.756 --> 00:12:08.566 A:middle
it's used to format numbers

00:12:08.566 --> 00:12:09.306 A:middle
instead of dates.

00:12:10.296 --> 00:12:12.316 A:middle
So for population I can simply

00:12:12.316 --> 00:12:13.976 A:middle
set my formatter's number style

00:12:13.976 --> 00:12:16.066 A:middle
to decimal and I set "uses

00:12:16.066 --> 00:12:17.396 A:middle
grouping separator" to "true,"

00:12:17.896 --> 00:12:19.426 A:middle
which makes it easier to read by

00:12:19.426 --> 00:12:20.636 A:middle
separating the number by the

00:12:20.636 --> 00:12:21.906 A:middle
thousands, and that's because

00:12:21.936 --> 00:12:23.406 A:middle
population tends to be a large

00:12:23.446 --> 00:12:24.000 A:middle
number.

00:12:26.046 --> 00:12:30.246 A:middle
For GDP I can also use a number

00:12:30.246 --> 00:12:31.996 A:middle
formatter, except this time I

00:12:31.996 --> 00:12:33.196 A:middle
would set the number style to

00:12:33.196 --> 00:12:35.396 A:middle
currency and the currency code

00:12:35.396 --> 00:12:36.896 A:middle
to US dollars because our data

00:12:36.896 --> 00:12:38.286 A:middle
is in US dollars.

00:12:38.876 --> 00:12:41.936 A:middle
And finally, for the literacy

00:12:41.936 --> 00:12:43.666 A:middle
percentage cell, as well as my

00:12:43.666 --> 00:12:45.696 A:middle
language population, I set the

00:12:45.696 --> 00:12:48.636 A:middle
number style to percent and I

00:12:48.906 --> 00:12:50.446 A:middle
give it a maximum and minimum

00:12:50.446 --> 00:12:51.896 A:middle
fraction digits to make sure it

00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:52.646 A:middle
looks consistent.

00:12:54.216 --> 00:12:55.266 A:middle
So now that my strings are

00:12:55.266 --> 00:12:57.206 A:middle
localizable and I'm displaying

00:12:57.206 --> 00:12:58.816 A:middle
my numbers -- and I'm formatting

00:12:58.816 --> 00:13:00.726 A:middle
my numbers correctly, the next

00:13:00.726 --> 00:13:02.156 A:middle
thing I want to do is make sure

00:13:02.156 --> 00:13:03.966 A:middle
my user interface is also ready.

00:13:04.856 --> 00:13:07.516 A:middle
And to do that I'm going to open

00:13:07.516 --> 00:13:10.226 A:middle
my main storyboard and I want to

00:13:10.226 --> 00:13:12.526 A:middle
show you how you can use pseudo

00:13:12.526 --> 00:13:14.316 A:middle
languages in Interface Builder

00:13:14.316 --> 00:13:17.276 A:middle
Preview to test your app for

00:13:17.666 --> 00:13:18.396 A:middle
localization.

00:13:19.236 --> 00:13:20.986 A:middle
So first I'll click on the top

00:13:20.986 --> 00:13:22.766 A:middle
right corner on the Assistant

00:13:22.766 --> 00:13:23.876 A:middle
Editor icon.

00:13:24.776 --> 00:13:26.536 A:middle
And then under this dropdown I

00:13:26.536 --> 00:13:28.136 A:middle
want to choose "preview" and

00:13:29.076 --> 00:13:30.326 A:middle
basically it's showing me a

00:13:30.326 --> 00:13:31.716 A:middle
preview of my storyboard.

00:13:32.856 --> 00:13:34.336 A:middle
And on the bottom, right corner

00:13:35.606 --> 00:13:38.436 A:middle
I get a language chooser and if

00:13:38.436 --> 00:13:39.756 A:middle
I had any localizations on my

00:13:39.756 --> 00:13:41.836 A:middle
project I would see those here,

00:13:42.216 --> 00:13:43.996 A:middle
but in this case it's showing me

00:13:44.426 --> 00:13:46.226 A:middle
all the pseudo language options

00:13:46.226 --> 00:13:47.346 A:middle
I can use in the preview.

00:13:48.286 --> 00:13:49.516 A:middle
So new in Xcode 9 we've

00:13:49.516 --> 00:13:50.846 A:middle
introduced a fixed pseudo

00:13:50.846 --> 00:13:51.226 A:middle
language.

00:13:51.226 --> 00:13:52.486 A:middle
So I'm going to select that to

00:13:52.486 --> 00:13:53.146 A:middle
see what it does.

00:13:54.326 --> 00:13:55.806 A:middle
As you can see it simply added

00:13:55.806 --> 00:13:57.226 A:middle
those square brackets and the

00:13:57.226 --> 00:13:58.776 A:middle
pound symbol before and after

00:13:58.776 --> 00:13:59.446 A:middle
each string.

00:14:00.606 --> 00:14:02.166 A:middle
And that makes it really easy to

00:14:02.166 --> 00:14:03.736 A:middle
spot if something is clipping or

00:14:03.736 --> 00:14:05.326 A:middle
not fitting in my UI because

00:14:05.566 --> 00:14:06.706 A:middle
those symbols would be missing.

00:14:07.446 --> 00:14:08.706 A:middle
So in this case it looks like my

00:14:08.706 --> 00:14:10.006 A:middle
button on the bottom doesn't

00:14:10.006 --> 00:14:11.316 A:middle
have the pound symbol and that's

00:14:11.316 --> 00:14:12.856 A:middle
the first thing I saw, but if

00:14:12.856 --> 00:14:14.096 A:middle
you take a closer look, even --

00:14:14.096 --> 00:14:15.646 A:middle
the y is clipping in "play."

00:14:15.646 --> 00:14:17.436 A:middle
So I'm going to go back to my

00:14:17.436 --> 00:14:19.746 A:middle
storyboard and see why that is.

00:14:21.156 --> 00:14:22.606 A:middle
And it looks like I have a fixed

00:14:22.606 --> 00:14:24.196 A:middle
width constraint, which in this

00:14:24.196 --> 00:14:25.656 A:middle
case is not necessary and

00:14:25.656 --> 00:14:26.916 A:middle
generally fixed width

00:14:26.916 --> 00:14:29.936 A:middle
constraints on text controls are

00:14:29.936 --> 00:14:31.636 A:middle
a bad idea for localization.

00:14:32.566 --> 00:14:34.846 A:middle
So if I get rid of it you'll see

00:14:34.846 --> 00:14:36.466 A:middle
that my pseudo language looks

00:14:36.466 --> 00:14:38.966 A:middle
exactly as expected and now I

00:14:39.636 --> 00:14:41.296 A:middle
know that I'm not going to be

00:14:41.296 --> 00:14:42.000 A:middle
clipping anything.

00:14:43.236 --> 00:14:45.556 A:middle
So these interface builder

00:14:45.556 --> 00:14:47.186 A:middle
previews are even more helpful

00:14:47.186 --> 00:14:48.406 A:middle
if you have more of your UI

00:14:48.406 --> 00:14:49.756 A:middle
defined in your storyboard.

00:14:50.466 --> 00:14:52.436 A:middle
In my case, a lot of my UI is

00:14:52.436 --> 00:14:53.616 A:middle
loaded in my table view

00:14:53.616 --> 00:14:54.166 A:middle
controller.

00:14:54.776 --> 00:14:56.466 A:middle
So I also want to show how I can

00:14:56.466 --> 00:14:58.286 A:middle
use pseudo languages at runtime

00:14:58.286 --> 00:14:58.906 A:middle
to test that.

00:15:00.716 --> 00:15:02.526 A:middle
So if I select -- if I click on

00:15:02.526 --> 00:15:04.466 A:middle
my scheme and select "edit

00:15:04.466 --> 00:15:06.466 A:middle
scheme" -- and make sure you

00:15:06.466 --> 00:15:07.516 A:middle
have "run" selected in the

00:15:07.516 --> 00:15:09.856 A:middle
sidebar -- under "application

00:15:09.856 --> 00:15:10.946 A:middle
language" you get a list of

00:15:10.946 --> 00:15:12.206 A:middle
languages you can choose from,

00:15:12.776 --> 00:15:14.126 A:middle
but over at the bottom you have

00:15:14.126 --> 00:15:15.896 A:middle
a list of all the available

00:15:16.016 --> 00:15:17.596 A:middle
pseudo languages you can use as

00:15:17.596 --> 00:15:18.616 A:middle
well -- at runtime.

00:15:19.676 --> 00:15:20.796 A:middle
Another pseudo language we've

00:15:20.796 --> 00:15:22.826 A:middle
added in Xcode 9 is the accented

00:15:22.826 --> 00:15:23.656 A:middle
Latin pseudo language.

00:15:23.656 --> 00:15:24.976 A:middle
And if I go ahead and play that

00:15:25.476 --> 00:15:33.726 A:middle
--

00:15:34.226 --> 00:15:36.926 A:middle
My app will launch with accents

00:15:36.926 --> 00:15:38.556 A:middle
above and below each of my

00:15:38.556 --> 00:15:39.646 A:middle
localizable strings.

00:15:40.296 --> 00:15:41.806 A:middle
And what this really helps with

00:15:41.806 --> 00:15:43.446 A:middle
is it gives me a preview of what

00:15:43.446 --> 00:15:44.956 A:middle
my app -- how my app would

00:15:44.956 --> 00:15:46.476 A:middle
handle languages that use a lot

00:15:46.476 --> 00:15:49.286 A:middle
of accents, diacritics, or even

00:15:49.286 --> 00:15:51.096 A:middle
languages where the scripted

00:15:51.096 --> 00:15:52.796 A:middle
self is generally taller than

00:15:52.796 --> 00:15:53.966 A:middle
English -- like Thai for

00:15:53.966 --> 00:15:54.396 A:middle
example.

00:15:55.096 --> 00:15:56.786 A:middle
So I can quickly scan this and

00:15:56.786 --> 00:15:58.286 A:middle
make sure that everything's

00:15:58.326 --> 00:16:00.056 A:middle
fitting vertically and I'm not

00:16:00.056 --> 00:16:02.926 A:middle
seeing any clippings.

00:16:02.966 --> 00:16:05.316 A:middle
And everything looks good here.

00:16:05.386 --> 00:16:08.936 A:middle
And then finally one more pseudo

00:16:09.046 --> 00:16:10.736 A:middle
language I'd like to show you at

00:16:10.736 --> 00:16:13.666 A:middle
runtime is the new right to left

00:16:13.666 --> 00:16:14.856 A:middle
pseudo language with right to

00:16:14.856 --> 00:16:15.476 A:middle
left strings.

00:16:16.876 --> 00:16:18.416 A:middle
And this pseudo language is very

00:16:18.416 --> 00:16:19.726 A:middle
helpful in testing whether your

00:16:19.726 --> 00:16:21.866 A:middle
app is ready for right to left

00:16:21.866 --> 00:16:23.616 A:middle
languages like Arabic and Hebrew

00:16:23.956 --> 00:16:25.316 A:middle
where the text itself is written

00:16:25.316 --> 00:16:26.076 A:middle
from right to left.

00:16:26.656 --> 00:16:28.096 A:middle
So as you can see, my UI

00:16:28.096 --> 00:16:29.866 A:middle
controls are already adjusted

00:16:29.866 --> 00:16:32.406 A:middle
and mirrored to look the way

00:16:32.406 --> 00:16:34.366 A:middle
they would look in a right to

00:16:34.366 --> 00:16:35.326 A:middle
left localization.

00:16:35.996 --> 00:16:37.606 A:middle
And what we also do is we

00:16:37.606 --> 00:16:39.406 A:middle
display the localizable strings

00:16:39.406 --> 00:16:40.176 A:middle
from right to left.

00:16:40.176 --> 00:16:41.946 A:middle
So the letters themselves have

00:16:41.946 --> 00:16:43.816 A:middle
flipped order and that really

00:16:43.816 --> 00:16:46.466 A:middle
helps give you an idea -- or put

00:16:46.466 --> 00:16:47.836 A:middle
you in the mindset of somebody

00:16:47.836 --> 00:16:49.616 A:middle
who reads their text from right

00:16:49.616 --> 00:16:50.526 A:middle
to left.

00:16:51.056 --> 00:16:52.806 A:middle
So these are some of the pseudo

00:16:52.806 --> 00:16:53.996 A:middle
languages.

00:16:54.516 --> 00:16:55.886 A:middle
I highly encourage you to try

00:16:55.886 --> 00:16:56.336 A:middle
them all.

00:16:56.506 --> 00:16:57.946 A:middle
They're very helpful to test

00:16:57.946 --> 00:16:59.426 A:middle
your app before you even add

00:16:59.426 --> 00:16:59.976 A:middle
localization.

00:17:03.456 --> 00:17:04.446 A:middle
And to summarize the

00:17:04.446 --> 00:17:06.006 A:middle
internationalization process;

00:17:06.866 --> 00:17:08.596 A:middle
first make sure you're using

00:17:08.596 --> 00:17:10.076 A:middle
standard APIs to load

00:17:10.076 --> 00:17:11.916 A:middle
localizable strings as well as

00:17:11.956 --> 00:17:13.726 A:middle
to format your data, like dates

00:17:13.726 --> 00:17:14.186 A:middle
and numbers.

00:17:14.836 --> 00:17:18.436 A:middle
And make sure your app is using

00:17:18.436 --> 00:17:20.106 A:middle
base internationalization to

00:17:20.106 --> 00:17:21.866 A:middle
separate your UI from your

00:17:21.866 --> 00:17:23.126 A:middle
localizable content.

00:17:23.516 --> 00:17:25.136 A:middle
And, of course, use auto layout

00:17:25.136 --> 00:17:26.526 A:middle
in your UI to make sure that the

00:17:26.526 --> 00:17:28.846 A:middle
app itself is flexible and can

00:17:28.876 --> 00:17:31.156 A:middle
adapt to different translations.

00:17:32.496 --> 00:17:34.176 A:middle
And, finally, we showed a lot of

00:17:34.256 --> 00:17:35.706 A:middle
tools that can validate your

00:17:35.706 --> 00:17:38.016 A:middle
internationalization, like the

00:17:38.016 --> 00:17:39.656 A:middle
new pseudo languages we've added

00:17:39.656 --> 00:17:41.646 A:middle
and the auto layout warnings

00:17:41.676 --> 00:17:42.816 A:middle
that are coming soon in the

00:17:42.816 --> 00:17:43.536 A:middle
future seat.

00:17:44.556 --> 00:17:46.746 A:middle
So my app is internationalized

00:17:46.746 --> 00:17:48.386 A:middle
now and I'm ready to add my

00:17:48.386 --> 00:17:49.426 A:middle
first localization.

00:17:49.426 --> 00:17:51.286 A:middle
So I'm going to call Sarah back

00:17:51.286 --> 00:17:53.036 A:middle
up on stage to show us how to do

00:17:53.036 --> 00:17:54.366 A:middle
that since she's the expert on

00:17:54.596 --> 00:17:55.506 A:middle
the topic.

00:17:56.516 --> 00:18:01.500 A:middle
[ Applause ]

