And you can do that right from

00:18:11.526 --> 00:18:13.506 A:middle
Xcode from your project info and

00:18:13.506 --> 00:18:15.496 A:middle
you have over 100 languages to

00:18:15.496 --> 00:18:16.096 A:middle
choose from.

00:18:17.066 --> 00:18:18.306 A:middle
So now that you've added these

00:18:18.306 --> 00:18:19.616 A:middle
languages that you want to

00:18:19.616 --> 00:18:21.376 A:middle
support in your app, so to

00:18:21.376 --> 00:18:23.196 A:middle
generate the localizable content

00:18:23.246 --> 00:18:25.506 A:middle
for your translators Xcode will

00:18:25.506 --> 00:18:27.196 A:middle
find all the localizable

00:18:27.196 --> 00:18:28.866 A:middle
resources that you have in your

00:18:28.956 --> 00:18:30.926 A:middle
project, then when you export

00:18:30.926 --> 00:18:32.536 A:middle
your projects for localization

00:18:32.866 --> 00:18:34.746 A:middle
Xcode will extract the strings

00:18:34.846 --> 00:18:36.496 A:middle
from this localizable resources

00:18:36.856 --> 00:18:38.986 A:middle
and generate XLIFF files for

00:18:38.986 --> 00:18:40.326 A:middle
every single language that you

00:18:40.326 --> 00:18:40.896 A:middle
have added.

00:18:41.486 --> 00:18:43.176 A:middle
And XLIFF file is simply a

00:18:43.176 --> 00:18:45.546 A:middle
standard XML localization file

00:18:45.546 --> 00:18:47.126 A:middle
format that is standard in the

00:18:47.126 --> 00:18:48.366 A:middle
localization industry.

00:18:48.826 --> 00:18:50.616 A:middle
So if you send your XLIFF files

00:18:50.616 --> 00:18:51.916 A:middle
to one of the localizers they

00:18:52.076 --> 00:18:53.516 A:middle
will be already familiar with

00:18:53.516 --> 00:18:54.956 A:middle
the formats and how to work with

00:18:54.956 --> 00:18:55.116 A:middle
it.

00:18:56.276 --> 00:18:57.586 A:middle
So once your XLIFF files are

00:18:57.586 --> 00:18:59.546 A:middle
translated you can import them

00:18:59.546 --> 00:19:02.696 A:middle
back and Xcode will integrate

00:19:02.696 --> 00:19:04.716 A:middle
automatically your localized

00:19:04.716 --> 00:19:06.646 A:middle
text back into your project.

00:19:07.046 --> 00:19:08.436 A:middle
And that's the localization

00:19:08.436 --> 00:19:09.606 A:middle
process in Xcode.

00:19:09.786 --> 00:19:11.016 A:middle
It's very simple and

00:19:11.016 --> 00:19:11.736 A:middle
straightforward.

00:19:13.226 --> 00:19:15.266 A:middle
And new in Xcode 9 we are adding

00:19:15.326 --> 00:19:17.496 A:middle
support for exporting and

00:19:17.496 --> 00:19:19.836 A:middle
importing string dics file

00:19:20.006 --> 00:19:20.536 A:middle
formats.

00:19:21.516 --> 00:19:23.116 A:middle
So string dics is the powerful

00:19:23.116 --> 00:19:24.796 A:middle
tool that lets you handle

00:19:24.986 --> 00:19:26.996 A:middle
plurals and adaptive strings in

00:19:26.996 --> 00:19:27.556 A:middle
your app.

00:19:29.116 --> 00:19:31.646 A:middle
In Xcode 9 you can now add and

00:19:31.646 --> 00:19:33.646 A:middle
create string dictionaries right

00:19:33.646 --> 00:19:35.616 A:middle
from the file template list in

00:19:35.616 --> 00:19:37.926 A:middle
Xcode and that will generate an

00:19:37.926 --> 00:19:39.926 A:middle
editor for you where you can add

00:19:40.036 --> 00:19:41.966 A:middle
and edit your keys and values.

00:19:42.596 --> 00:19:45.446 A:middle
So now let's talk more in detail

00:19:45.446 --> 00:19:46.796 A:middle
about what can you do with

00:19:46.796 --> 00:19:48.246 A:middle
strings dictionaries and why

00:19:48.246 --> 00:19:48.986 A:middle
they are helpful.

00:19:49.936 --> 00:19:51.506 A:middle
So first strings dictionaries

00:19:51.506 --> 00:19:53.366 A:middle
can help you handle the

00:19:53.366 --> 00:19:54.966 A:middle
complexity of plural forms

00:19:54.966 --> 00:19:56.936 A:middle
without writing any code in your

00:19:57.556 --> 00:19:57.626 A:middle
app.

00:19:58.196 --> 00:20:00.236 A:middle
So let's assume I have this

00:20:00.236 --> 00:20:02.166 A:middle
logic in my code to handle

00:20:02.226 --> 00:20:03.106 A:middle
plural variants.

00:20:03.556 --> 00:20:05.066 A:middle
So here I have an array.

00:20:05.556 --> 00:20:07.206 A:middle
If the count of my array is one

00:20:07.596 --> 00:20:09.896 A:middle
I set my string to one popular

00:20:09.896 --> 00:20:10.486 A:middle
language.

00:20:10.846 --> 00:20:13.426 A:middle
Else if the count of my array is

00:20:13.426 --> 00:20:15.416 A:middle
more than one I set my string

00:20:15.416 --> 00:20:17.006 A:middle
here to something like person d

00:20:17.006 --> 00:20:19.276 A:middle
popular languages where person d

00:20:19.276 --> 00:20:20.576 A:middle
is a format string that will

00:20:20.576 --> 00:20:22.136 A:middle
replace the runtime with the

00:20:22.176 --> 00:20:23.116 A:middle
count of my array.

00:20:23.906 --> 00:20:26.166 A:middle
So this logic might work -- well

00:20:26.166 --> 00:20:27.916 A:middle
it would work for a language

00:20:27.916 --> 00:20:29.256 A:middle
like English where there are

00:20:29.386 --> 00:20:31.096 A:middle
only two plural forms; one

00:20:31.096 --> 00:20:32.296 A:middle
singular and one plural.

00:20:33.386 --> 00:20:34.626 A:middle
But this would be a complete

00:20:34.626 --> 00:20:36.436 A:middle
disaster for a language like

00:20:36.626 --> 00:20:38.046 A:middle
Russian where there are more

00:20:38.046 --> 00:20:39.126 A:middle
plural variants.

00:20:39.546 --> 00:20:41.056 A:middle
So Russian has four different

00:20:41.056 --> 00:20:42.616 A:middle
plural variants and your

00:20:42.756 --> 00:20:44.216 A:middle
translators need to think about

00:20:44.456 --> 00:20:46.166 A:middle
work arounds and ways on how to

00:20:46.166 --> 00:20:47.536 A:middle
translate all these variants

00:20:47.536 --> 00:20:49.506 A:middle
with the one generic plural that

00:20:49.746 --> 00:20:50.886 A:middle
you provided -- the one you are

00:20:50.886 --> 00:20:52.746 A:middle
using for English, which will

00:20:52.806 --> 00:20:56.256 A:middle
make basically your translations

00:20:56.256 --> 00:20:57.626 A:middle
sound robotic and not very

00:20:57.626 --> 00:20:59.256 A:middle
natural for a native speaker.

00:20:59.516 --> 00:21:03.006 A:middle
So this example here sounds like

00:21:03.006 --> 00:21:04.636 A:middle
something; "popular languages

00:21:04.636 --> 00:21:06.096 A:middle
column one, popular languages

00:21:06.166 --> 00:21:07.506 A:middle
column two," and you don't want

00:21:07.586 --> 00:21:09.156 A:middle
that in your app.

00:21:09.306 --> 00:21:10.416 A:middle
So to solve this kind of

00:21:10.516 --> 00:21:13.436 A:middle
problem, when we're done writing

00:21:13.436 --> 00:21:15.126 A:middle
any code you can just use

00:21:15.386 --> 00:21:16.306 A:middle
strings dictionaries.

00:21:17.246 --> 00:21:18.786 A:middle
So all you need to do in your

00:21:18.786 --> 00:21:20.816 A:middle
strings dics file -- so you need

00:21:20.816 --> 00:21:23.186 A:middle
to add your localized format

00:21:23.186 --> 00:21:23.456 A:middle
key.

00:21:24.296 --> 00:21:25.876 A:middle
In this example my localized

00:21:25.876 --> 00:21:27.446 A:middle
format key is "languages."

00:21:27.986 --> 00:21:30.566 A:middle
Then you need to add the plural

00:21:30.566 --> 00:21:32.256 A:middle
variants that are relevant for

00:21:32.256 --> 00:21:34.596 A:middle
your development language.

00:21:34.756 --> 00:21:36.176 A:middle
So since here my development

00:21:36.176 --> 00:21:37.936 A:middle
language is English, I only care

00:21:37.936 --> 00:21:39.726 A:middle
about two plural variants, one

00:21:39.726 --> 00:21:40.246 A:middle
and other.

00:21:40.246 --> 00:21:41.896 A:middle
So one is for the singular case

00:21:42.186 --> 00:21:43.736 A:middle
and other is for the plural

00:21:43.736 --> 00:21:44.046 A:middle
case.

00:21:45.526 --> 00:21:47.596 A:middle
Then by wrapping your plural

00:21:47.706 --> 00:21:49.436 A:middle
string with NS Localized String,

00:21:49.826 --> 00:21:51.876 A:middle
as you will do with any other

00:21:52.416 --> 00:21:53.386 A:middle
string that you have in your

00:21:53.446 --> 00:21:55.246 A:middle
code, when you export your

00:21:55.286 --> 00:21:57.046 A:middle
projects for localization, Xcode

00:21:57.046 --> 00:21:59.126 A:middle
will generate automatically for

00:21:59.126 --> 00:22:01.046 A:middle
you the plural keys for other

00:22:01.046 --> 00:22:02.306 A:middle
languages that you support.

00:22:02.816 --> 00:22:05.576 A:middle
So the variance for other

00:22:05.576 --> 00:22:07.126 A:middle
languages will be included in

00:22:07.126 --> 00:22:08.826 A:middle
your XK files and your

00:22:08.926 --> 00:22:09.866 A:middle
translators when they are

00:22:10.016 --> 00:22:11.496 A:middle
translating the strings they

00:22:11.496 --> 00:22:13.256 A:middle
will find the plural variants

00:22:13.256 --> 00:22:14.536 A:middle
that are relevant for the

00:22:14.536 --> 00:22:15.086 A:middle
language.

00:22:15.596 --> 00:22:17.166 A:middle
And now our translation will be

00:22:17.166 --> 00:22:18.736 A:middle
correct and your users will have

00:22:18.736 --> 00:22:20.296 A:middle
more grammatically correct

00:22:20.296 --> 00:22:21.016 A:middle
translations.

00:22:21.756 --> 00:22:23.436 A:middle
So this is Strings Dics support

00:22:23.436 --> 00:22:26.426 A:middle
for Plural Variants in Xcode 9.

00:22:27.106 --> 00:22:28.776 A:middle
Another thing you can do with

00:22:28.776 --> 00:22:30.666 A:middle
strings dictionaries in Xcode 9

00:22:30.666 --> 00:22:32.536 A:middle
is support for adaptive strings.

00:22:33.456 --> 00:22:36.256 A:middle
So if we take this example from

00:22:36.576 --> 00:22:39.316 A:middle
Ia's app earlier, she had a

00:22:39.316 --> 00:22:41.166 A:middle
string here called "Gross

00:22:41.236 --> 00:22:42.696 A:middle
Domestic Products in Billions,"

00:22:42.696 --> 00:22:44.066 A:middle
which is kind of long, but it

00:22:44.066 --> 00:22:45.406 A:middle
fits fine on an iPad because

00:22:45.406 --> 00:22:46.816 A:middle
there is enough space for it.

00:22:47.636 --> 00:22:49.366 A:middle
If we run the app again in a

00:22:49.366 --> 00:22:51.546 A:middle
smaller device like an iPhone 7

00:22:52.436 --> 00:22:53.716 A:middle
-- so this string does not fit

00:22:53.716 --> 00:22:54.206 A:middle
anymore.

00:22:54.306 --> 00:22:55.616 A:middle
As you can see on the screen,

00:22:55.616 --> 00:22:56.936 A:middle
the number on the right side now

00:22:56.986 --> 00:22:58.566 A:middle
shrinks and you can only read

00:22:58.566 --> 00:22:59.606 A:middle
the three first characters,

00:22:59.606 --> 00:23:00.766 A:middle
which is kind of wrong because

00:23:00.766 --> 00:23:01.486 A:middle
we are given the wrong

00:23:01.486 --> 00:23:02.626 A:middle
information to the user.

00:23:03.706 --> 00:23:05.736 A:middle
So you can take advantage of

00:23:06.186 --> 00:23:07.866 A:middle
strings dictionaries again to

00:23:07.866 --> 00:23:09.216 A:middle
solve these kinds of problems

00:23:09.476 --> 00:23:10.996 A:middle
and provide different string

00:23:10.996 --> 00:23:12.486 A:middle
variants for your app.

00:23:13.166 --> 00:23:14.506 A:middle
So here I have three different

00:23:14.506 --> 00:23:17.086 A:middle
keys; 20, 25, and 50.

00:23:17.366 --> 00:23:18.556 A:middle
They correspond to different

00:23:18.556 --> 00:23:19.336 A:middle
screen sizes.

00:23:19.336 --> 00:23:21.586 A:middle
And then I have the strings that

00:23:21.586 --> 00:23:23.246 A:middle
I want to show for every screen

00:23:23.246 --> 00:23:23.606 A:middle
size.

00:23:24.346 --> 00:23:26.586 A:middle
So if you call NS Localized

00:23:26.676 --> 00:23:28.796 A:middle
Strings on the key within your

00:23:28.796 --> 00:23:29.736 A:middle
strings dics file.

00:23:30.386 --> 00:23:31.706 A:middle
So you enable -- we pick the

00:23:31.706 --> 00:23:34.096 A:middle
right value for you at runtime

00:23:34.196 --> 00:23:36.266 A:middle
based on the space available on

00:23:36.266 --> 00:23:36.826 A:middle
the screen.

00:23:37.856 --> 00:23:39.596 A:middle
So if you are not using UI label

00:23:39.596 --> 00:23:40.606 A:middle
and you are using a custom

00:23:40.606 --> 00:23:42.626 A:middle
control of your own, you can

00:23:42.626 --> 00:23:44.196 A:middle
still take advantage of the

00:23:44.196 --> 00:23:46.096 A:middle
functionality by calling

00:23:46.236 --> 00:23:47.926 A:middle
variance fit in presentation

00:23:47.926 --> 00:23:50.476 A:middle
with API, where you pass in one

00:23:50.476 --> 00:23:51.496 A:middle
of the keys that you have

00:23:51.496 --> 00:23:53.146 A:middle
defined in your strings dics

00:23:53.146 --> 00:23:54.956 A:middle
file and then at runtime this

00:23:54.956 --> 00:23:56.446 A:middle
will choose the right value for

00:23:56.446 --> 00:23:57.746 A:middle
you that corresponds to that

00:23:57.746 --> 00:23:57.876 A:middle
key.

00:23:58.646 --> 00:24:00.696 A:middle
And we will be providing the

00:24:00.696 --> 00:24:02.186 A:middle
keys and the corresponding

00:24:02.186 --> 00:24:03.266 A:middle
screen sizes in the

00:24:03.266 --> 00:24:04.756 A:middle
documentation if you would like

00:24:04.756 --> 00:24:05.746 A:middle
to check out that later.

00:24:07.046 --> 00:24:09.156 A:middle
So now if we run again the app

00:24:09.346 --> 00:24:11.036 A:middle
on the iPad, still using the

00:24:11.036 --> 00:24:13.556 A:middle
full string, and if we run it

00:24:13.556 --> 00:24:15.196 A:middle
again in a smaller device like

00:24:15.196 --> 00:24:17.226 A:middle
an iPhone 7 now we pick the

00:24:17.226 --> 00:24:18.546 A:middle
right variant that will fit

00:24:18.716 --> 00:24:20.486 A:middle
nicely on the screen size.

00:24:21.286 --> 00:24:22.316 A:middle
And thus without erasing a

00:24:22.396 --> 00:24:23.946 A:middle
single line of code your app

00:24:23.946 --> 00:24:26.066 A:middle
looks nice and beautiful in all

00:24:26.196 --> 00:24:27.526 A:middle
different screen sizes and

00:24:27.526 --> 00:24:29.316 A:middle
configurations of your app.

00:24:29.316 --> 00:24:30.776 A:middle
And adaptive strings are really

00:24:30.776 --> 00:24:32.496 A:middle
helpful if you are supporting

00:24:32.496 --> 00:24:33.726 A:middle
localizations in your app

00:24:33.856 --> 00:24:34.896 A:middle
because you might have some

00:24:34.896 --> 00:24:36.466 A:middle
languages that are longer or

00:24:36.466 --> 00:24:38.056 A:middle
shorter than others and you want

00:24:38.056 --> 00:24:39.426 A:middle
to give this flexibility to your

00:24:39.426 --> 00:24:41.496 A:middle
translators to provide like

00:24:41.496 --> 00:24:42.686 A:middle
adaptive strings for the

00:24:42.686 --> 00:24:43.216 A:middle
language.

00:24:44.936 --> 00:24:46.266 A:middle
So now that you're done with

00:24:46.266 --> 00:24:48.316 A:middle
supporting plural support as

00:24:48.316 --> 00:24:50.286 A:middle
well as adaptive strings you are

00:24:50.286 --> 00:24:52.556 A:middle
ready to localize your app.

00:24:52.556 --> 00:24:53.516 A:middle
And the first step in

00:24:53.516 --> 00:24:55.926 A:middle
localization is exporting your

00:24:55.926 --> 00:24:56.596 A:middle
project.

00:24:57.006 --> 00:24:58.326 A:middle
So when you export your projects

00:24:58.326 --> 00:25:00.126 A:middle
for localization -- so Xcode

00:25:00.126 --> 00:25:01.436 A:middle
will ask you which languages you

00:25:01.436 --> 00:25:02.966 A:middle
want to localize first.

00:25:03.006 --> 00:25:04.506 A:middle
So once you pick the language

00:25:04.506 --> 00:25:06.386 A:middle
you want Xcode will generate

00:25:06.526 --> 00:25:09.076 A:middle
XLIFF files for you to send to

00:25:09.186 --> 00:25:09.806 A:middle
your translators.

00:25:10.236 --> 00:25:11.516 A:middle
So once your XLIFF files are

00:25:11.636 --> 00:25:14.026 A:middle
translated you can import them

00:25:14.026 --> 00:25:16.196 A:middle
back in your project and Xcode

00:25:16.196 --> 00:25:17.646 A:middle
will show you this nice diff

00:25:17.926 --> 00:25:19.796 A:middle
with what was changed by your

00:25:19.926 --> 00:25:20.616 A:middle
translators.

00:25:22.176 --> 00:25:24.046 A:middle
And after that Xcode will just

00:25:24.046 --> 00:25:25.416 A:middle
integrate your localized text

00:25:25.576 --> 00:25:27.136 A:middle
back into your project and your

00:25:27.136 --> 00:25:28.886 A:middle
strings will be localized.

00:25:29.436 --> 00:25:31.616 A:middle
So now that your strings are

00:25:31.616 --> 00:25:33.126 A:middle
localized, what about other

00:25:33.126 --> 00:25:34.636 A:middle
resources that are not string

00:25:34.636 --> 00:25:36.986 A:middle
based that you want -- probably

00:25:36.986 --> 00:25:38.136 A:middle
you want to localize, like

00:25:38.136 --> 00:25:39.566 A:middle
images or audio files?

00:25:39.656 --> 00:25:42.036 A:middle
So you might have something like

00:25:42.036 --> 00:25:44.336 A:middle
this, an image that has text on

00:25:44.366 --> 00:25:46.136 A:middle
it, and you want to provide an

00:25:46.136 --> 00:25:47.566 A:middle
alternative image for other

00:25:47.566 --> 00:25:48.186 A:middle
languages.

00:25:48.616 --> 00:25:50.256 A:middle
So you can localize other

00:25:50.536 --> 00:25:52.866 A:middle
resources in Xcode easily by

00:25:52.866 --> 00:25:54.346 A:middle
clicking the "localize" button

00:25:54.346 --> 00:25:55.786 A:middle
in the "file inspector."

00:25:56.336 --> 00:25:58.356 A:middle
Again Xcode will ask you which

00:25:58.356 --> 00:25:59.576 A:middle
language you want to localize

00:25:59.576 --> 00:26:00.426 A:middle
this asset for.

00:26:00.426 --> 00:26:02.066 A:middle
You can pick from the list of

00:26:02.146 --> 00:26:04.426 A:middle
your languages and Xcode will

00:26:04.426 --> 00:26:06.436 A:middle
move this asset to the specific

00:26:06.436 --> 00:26:08.326 A:middle
language folder where you can

00:26:08.326 --> 00:26:09.916 A:middle
replace it with the image or the

00:26:09.996 --> 00:26:11.546 A:middle
asset that you want to show for

00:26:11.546 --> 00:26:12.346 A:middle
that language.

00:26:13.166 --> 00:26:14.756 A:middle
So this is the localization

00:26:14.756 --> 00:26:16.196 A:middle
workflow in Xcode 9.

00:26:16.646 --> 00:26:19.186 A:middle
So we saw how to support plurals

00:26:19.276 --> 00:26:21.056 A:middle
as well as adaptive strings and

00:26:21.056 --> 00:26:22.586 A:middle
how to localize other resources.

00:26:23.006 --> 00:26:24.286 A:middle
And with that I would like to

00:26:24.326 --> 00:26:26.256 A:middle
call Chris on stage to give you

00:26:26.256 --> 00:26:26.586 A:middle
a demo.

00:26:26.586 --> 00:26:26.916 A:middle
Thank you.

