00:32:49.236 --> 00:32:51.466 A:middle
So, to summarize, strings dicts

00:32:51.466 --> 00:32:53.176 A:middle
are really powerful and you can

00:32:53.176 --> 00:32:55.366 A:middle
use them for pluralization and

00:32:55.426 --> 00:32:57.276 A:middle
for adaptive width strings in

00:32:57.276 --> 00:32:59.016 A:middle
your applications to ensure that

00:32:59.016 --> 00:33:01.326 A:middle
they look right not only based

00:33:01.326 --> 00:33:03.036 A:middle
on the user's language, but also

00:33:03.036 --> 00:33:04.196 A:middle
based on their device width.

00:33:06.166 --> 00:33:08.216 A:middle
It's easy to export an XLIFF

00:33:08.316 --> 00:33:10.456 A:middle
from your Xcode application for

00:33:10.456 --> 00:33:13.516 A:middle
your localization process and to

00:33:13.576 --> 00:33:15.356 A:middle
import your translated strings

00:33:15.356 --> 00:33:17.396 A:middle
via XLIFF back into your

00:33:17.396 --> 00:33:19.216 A:middle
application's Xcode project.

