00:33:56.436 --> 00:33:58.586 A:middle
New in Xcode 9 we've introduced

00:33:58.586 --> 00:34:00.356 A:middle
the ability to specify the

00:34:00.356 --> 00:34:02.376 A:middle
application language and region

00:34:02.526 --> 00:34:03.556 A:middle
that you would like to run your

00:34:03.556 --> 00:34:04.156 A:middle
tests in.

00:34:04.706 --> 00:34:06.096 A:middle
And you can do this in the test

00:34:06.166 --> 00:34:07.896 A:middle
scheme editor right in Xcode.

00:34:08.356 --> 00:34:11.496 A:middle
And today I want to talk about

00:34:11.496 --> 00:34:13.146 A:middle
UI testing with XC test.

00:34:14.086 --> 00:34:16.226 A:middle
So UI testing is a great way for

00:34:16.226 --> 00:34:17.496 A:middle
you to validate both your

00:34:17.496 --> 00:34:19.446 A:middle
application's UI as well as its

00:34:19.446 --> 00:34:20.166 A:middle
functionality.

00:34:21.336 --> 00:34:23.326 A:middle
Let's take this line of code on

00:34:23.326 --> 00:34:24.316 A:middle
the screen for example.

00:34:25.466 --> 00:34:26.666 A:middle
This is what you would write to

00:34:26.666 --> 00:34:28.886 A:middle
simulate tapping on a table cell

00:34:28.886 --> 00:34:30.496 A:middle
that has the text territory in

00:34:31.236 --> 00:34:31.306 A:middle
it.

00:34:32.166 --> 00:34:33.706 A:middle
Now that's not going to work for

00:34:33.706 --> 00:34:35.866 A:middle
localization because that text

00:34:35.866 --> 00:34:37.526 A:middle
is going to be translated into

00:34:37.526 --> 00:34:38.856 A:middle
each language that you run your

00:34:38.856 --> 00:34:39.386 A:middle
test in.

00:34:40.036 --> 00:34:41.476 A:middle
And additionally, if you decide

00:34:41.476 --> 00:34:42.726 A:middle
to go and change the wording in

00:34:42.726 --> 00:34:43.836 A:middle
your app, even in your

00:34:43.836 --> 00:34:45.296 A:middle
development language -- like

00:34:45.296 --> 00:34:46.286 A:middle
let's say I want to call it

00:34:46.286 --> 00:34:47.356 A:middle
"region" now instead of

00:34:47.356 --> 00:34:49.086 A:middle
"territory," you don't really

00:34:49.086 --> 00:34:50.926 A:middle
want to go back and update every

00:34:50.926 --> 00:34:52.406 A:middle
single test that you've written

00:34:52.526 --> 00:34:53.866 A:middle
just so that it can start

00:34:53.866 --> 00:34:54.566 A:middle
succeeding again.

00:34:55.536 --> 00:34:57.136 A:middle
So instead, what we recommend

00:34:57.136 --> 00:34:58.726 A:middle
you do is use accessibility

00:34:58.726 --> 00:34:59.436 A:middle
identifiers.

00:35:00.766 --> 00:35:02.376 A:middle
These identifiers are unique to

00:35:02.376 --> 00:35:04.456 A:middle
every element on your screen and

00:35:04.456 --> 00:35:06.616 A:middle
you can use them to find these

00:35:06.616 --> 00:35:08.006 A:middle
elements without really knowing

00:35:08.006 --> 00:35:08.886 A:middle
what strings are loaded into

00:35:08.886 --> 00:35:08.976 A:middle
them.

00:35:14.046 --> 00:35:15.526 A:middle
So to set the accessibility

00:35:15.526 --> 00:35:17.406 A:middle
identifier, you can simply set

00:35:17.406 --> 00:35:19.296 A:middle
the property on your UI control

00:35:19.296 --> 00:35:20.916 A:middle
when create it, or your NS

00:35:20.916 --> 00:35:21.286 A:middle
control.

00:35:23.086 --> 00:35:24.726 A:middle
Or if you're loading your UI

00:35:24.726 --> 00:35:26.486 A:middle
from a storyboard or a zip file

00:35:26.606 --> 00:35:28.016 A:middle
you can set it in the identity

00:35:28.016 --> 00:35:29.626 A:middle
inspector in interface builder.

00:35:30.226 --> 00:35:33.726 A:middle
So now that your tests are

00:35:33.726 --> 00:35:35.016 A:middle
localization friendly and

00:35:35.016 --> 00:35:36.566 A:middle
they're succeeding in all the

00:35:36.566 --> 00:35:37.756 A:middle
languages that you support,

00:35:38.776 --> 00:35:40.176 A:middle
there's even more that you can

00:35:40.176 --> 00:35:42.066 A:middle
do to take advantage of that.

00:35:42.906 --> 00:35:44.386 A:middle
We're introducing -- this year

00:35:44.436 --> 00:35:46.006 A:middle
we're introducing XCT attachment

00:35:46.006 --> 00:35:48.096 A:middle
APIs, which allow you to attach

00:35:48.226 --> 00:35:49.996 A:middle
screen shots as well as any

00:35:49.996 --> 00:35:51.616 A:middle
other data you collect during

00:35:51.616 --> 00:35:54.466 A:middle
your test and it'll attach it to

00:35:54.586 --> 00:35:55.926 A:middle
your test report at the end.

00:35:56.766 --> 00:35:58.346 A:middle
What this empowers you to do is

00:35:58.346 --> 00:36:00.276 A:middle
get a full coverage of your UI.

00:36:00.906 --> 00:36:02.886 A:middle
So every screen in your app, in

00:36:02.886 --> 00:36:04.236 A:middle
every localization that you

00:36:04.236 --> 00:36:06.726 A:middle
support, as well as every device

00:36:06.726 --> 00:36:07.416 A:middle
that you support.

00:36:07.696 --> 00:36:09.116 A:middle
And you can do all that while

00:36:09.116 --> 00:36:11.786 A:middle
writing only one test -- well,

00:36:11.946 --> 00:36:13.836 A:middle
one test for each thing you want

00:36:14.936 --> 00:36:16.136 A:middle
to test.

00:36:16.136 --> 00:36:16.936 A:middle
[laughing] To find out more

00:36:16.936 --> 00:36:19.256 A:middle
about XCT attachment and what

00:36:19.256 --> 00:36:21.346 A:middle
else is new in testing please

00:36:21.396 --> 00:36:23.906 A:middle
see those related sessions

00:36:23.946 --> 00:36:24.596 A:middle
throughout the week.

